## Here are the detailed steps and commands for creating a new Laravel project on your Ubuntu EC2 instance:
Step 1: Install Composer (if not installed)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install curl php-cli php-mbstring unzip zip php-xml php-bcmath php-curl php-mysql -y
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php
sudo mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer
composer --version





Step 2: Create a New Laravel Project
Choose a directory for your Laravel project under /var/www, for example myapp

sudo mkdir -p /var/www/myapp
sudo chown -R ubuntu:ubuntu /var/www/myapp
cd /var/www
composer create-project laravel/laravel myapp




























































